<HEADLINE>
FT  25 MAR 93 / UK Company News: Richardsons West
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Richardsons Westgarth, the steel stockholder and processor, achieved a rise
in 1992 pre-tax profits from Pounds 1.76m to Pounds 1.92m in an environment
described as 'generally hostile.'
A final dividend of 1.75p makes a 3p (2.9p) total. The shares responded with
an 8p rise to 77p.
Sales improved from Pounds 45.4m to Pounds 53.5m and included a seven
months' contribution from Tipton Steel Stock Holders (Stoke).
Higher tax of Pounds 647,000 (Pounds 234,000) left earnings at 4.6p (5.9p).
Assuming a 33 per cent tax charge earnings per share amounted to 4.7p
(4.5p).
</TEXT>
