<HEADLINE>
FT  25 MAR 93 / UK Company News: Arthur Wood
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Pre-tax profits of Arthur Wood &amp; Son (Longport), the Stoke-on-Trent maker of
earthenware, beakers and terracotta teapots, fell from Pounds 261,431 to
Pounds 76,882 for 1992.
The dividend for the year is cut from 4.1p to 1.5p. Earnings per share fell
to 2.79p (9.28p).
Turnover totalled Pounds 3.34m (Pounds 3.7m). The directors said there was a
high element of fixed costs in pottery manufacture and that any reduction in
turnover had a 'disproportionate effect on profits.'
