<HEADLINE>
FT  25 MAR 93 / UK Company News: Sea Containers
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Sea Containers, the Bermuda-based cargo equipment and ferry group, beat its
earnings per share forecast with a 4 cent rise to Dollars 2.35 (165p) for
1992.
For the final quarter the earnings figure of 28 cents compared with previous
losses of 4 cents.
Total revenue for the year grew to Dollars 421m (Dollars 385m). Net income
of Dollars 39.8m (Dollars 32.7m) was aided by an increased contribution of
Dollars 33.3m (Dollars 25.5m) from marine container leasing.
Ferry and port income fell Dollars 4m to Dollars 16.2m. Leisure industries
incurred a loss, but this was offset by profits from foreign exchange
contracts and left profit from other activities of Dollars 400,000 (Dollars
4.9m).
The company said the results were about Dollars 1m greater than predicted
due to year-end accounting adjustments.
</TEXT>
