<HEADLINE>
FT  25 MAR 93 / UK Company News: Templeton Emerging
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Templeton Emerging Markets Investment Trust is hoping to raise Pounds 85m
via a placing of shares with warrants attached. The trust specialises in
small stock markets in areas such as south-east Asia and Latin America.
The trust has frequently traded at a premium to net assets, an indication
that demand for shares exceeds supply. Existing shareholders have the right
to subscribe for new shares on the basis of one offer unit for every three
existing shares. The offer units, priced at 100p, will be converted into
ordinary shares using a formula based on net asset value.
