<HEADLINE>
FT  25 MAR 93 / UK Company News: Town Centre
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Mr Arnold Ziff, chairman of Town Centre Securities, the Leeds-based property
investment and development group, yesterday launched a stinging attack on
government policy regarding the rating of empty premises.
'This is probably the first time in history that any government has been so
stupid as to put a tax where there is no income.
'If the powers that be cannot realise the consequences of this iniquitous
tax . . . then there is little hope for the future of the building industry
in this country.'
Mr Ziff's statement accompanied the group's results for the six months to
December 31 which showed profits ahead 10 per cent to Pounds 3.65m (Pounds
3.31m) before tax.
The interim dividend goes up to 1.1p (1p), payable from earnings of 2.4p
(2.21p) per share.
</TEXT>
