<HEADLINE>
FT  24 MAR 93 / International Capital Markets: Egypt investment fund planned
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By MARK NICHOLSON
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   CAIRO
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
KIDDER Peabody, the Investment &amp; Securities Group of Egypt, and the
International Finance Corporation are to create a Dollars 50m investment
fund - the first direct investment fund in Egypt to be managed in the
country, writes Mark Nicholson in Cairo.
The fund, which its creators hope will be up and running by June this year,
will invest directly in Egyptian securities and private equity, offer
mezzanine capital to Egyptian companies, and possibly invest in
privatisation issues under the government's IMF and World Bank guided reform
programme.
The investment vehicle will be open to individuals and institutions for a
minimum subscription of Dollars 500,000.
