FT  24 MAR 93 / International Company News: Comparex earnings halved to
DM15bn
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By ALAN CANE
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
COMPAREX, the computer supplier wholly owned by BASF Group of Germany, saw
profits after tax halved last year as hardware prices continued to fall in
tough trading conditions.
Turnover for the year totalled DM1.14bn, (Dollars 695m) about 9 per cent
lower than last year and 6 per cent lower than forecast.
Profits after tax were DM15m, half last year's total. The company said the
result was satisfactory as profits margins in the computer industry had
eroded steadily as prices fell.
Comparex markets mainframe computers manufactured by Hitachi of Japan and
peripherals of its own design. Computing services contributed 19 per cent of
total revenues for 1992, 3 per cent up on the previous year.
