FT  24 MAR 93 / Polish business weekly launched
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By CHRISTOPHER BOBINSKI
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   WARSAW
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
RINGIER, the Swiss publisher and printing group, yesterday launched Cash, a
business weekly, in Poland, Christopher Bobinski reports from Warsaw. The
weekly is modelled on the original Cash first published in Switzerland in
1989 and on Profit, started in Czechoslovakia two years later. Profit now
sells 130,000 copies a week while Ringier's Polish weekly aims at a 350,000
circulation by next year. Ringier owns 18 more daily and weekly papers in
Slovakia and the Czech Republic.
