<HEADLINE>
FT  24 MAR 93 / International Company News: Gillette to post offer for
Parker Pen
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By NIKKI TAIT
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   NEW YORK
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
GILLETTE, the Boston-based toiletries and shaving products group, will post
its offer to acquire Parker Pen to shareholders of the UK company today,
after a US federal judge denied the US Justice Department's request for a
temporary restraining order.
The Justice Department announced on Monday that it was filing an anti-trust
suit, preventing Gillette from purchasing Parker Pen, on the grounds that
the deal would have an anti-competitive effect on the market for premium
fountain pens.
However, in spite of yesterday's ruling that Gillette can go ahead with the
posting of its Dollars 560m offer, a US court must still rule on the Justice
Department's request for a preliminary injunction barring the deal.
In the meantime, the US bidder - which is making its offer under UK takeover
rules, which incorporate a strict timetable for bids - will be unable to buy
shares in, or acquire control of, Parker Pen.
