<HEADLINE>
FT  24 MAR 93 / Russia in Crisis: Douglas Hurd to hold talks with US
officials
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
British foreign secretary Douglas Hurd will fly to Washington today for
talks with US officials expected to cover the problems facing Mr Yeltsin,
British officials said yesterday.
They said Mr Hurd would also discuss with Mr Christopher the conflict in
former Yugoslavia, North Korea's row with the United Nations over its
nuclear programme, Iraq, and US-European Community trade disputes.
It will be Mr Hurd's first full meeting with Mr Christopher, though both men
attended a meeting of Nato foreign ministers in Brussels last month.
During his two-day stay he will also meet national security adviser Anthony
Lake, deputy defence secretary William Perry and leading members of
Congress.
</TEXT>
