<HEADLINE>
FT  24 MAR 93 / World News in Brief: Letter bombs investigated
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Police were investigating two separate incidents involving letter bombs. The
first package exploded at the headquarters of Anglian Water at Huntingdon,
Cambridgeshire. The second device, at the Dounreay nuclear plant in
Scotland, was made safe.
