<HEADLINE>
FT  24 MAR 93 / Auditors must restructure profession
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
AUDITORS must restructure their profession radically or risk losing their
monopoly on scrutinising financial reports, Coopers &amp; Lybrand, the UK's
largest accountancy firm, warned yesterday.
Unless auditors develop long-term plans they will fail to attract
high-quality recruits and may lose their statutory monopoly on auditing to
other consultants, the firm added.
The conclusion comes in the firm's submission to the Auditing Practices
Board about its consultative document on the future development of auditing.
The submission's positive tone for reform is in stark contrast to many
submissions to the board, which have been highly critical of the proposals
for change.
Shareholders need to take a more active role in improving the development of
auditing, the Institute of Chartered Accountants of Scotland said in its
submission.
</TEXT>
