FT  24 MAR 93 / World Trade News: UK vending contract
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By GARY MEAD
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
FOUR SQUARE, a UK-based subsidiary of Mars, the US confectionery and petfood
multinational, has won a Pounds 50m contract to supply Apex of Japan with
33,000 tea and coffee vending machines, as well as drinks, over the next
three years.
Apex is a market leader in Japan, operating more than 50,000 office-based
drinks vending machines, with an annual turnover of Y7.3bn (Pounds 43m) in
1992. Japan has some 5.5m vending machines - about one for every 20 people -
and almost half are drinks dispensers.
Four Square, based at Basingstoke in the UK, is understood to have an annual
turnover in the region of Pounds 100m; the deal with Apex thus represents an
important boost to the company's revenues.
