<HEADLINE>
FT  24 MAR 93 / Go-ahead given for air ticket claims
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By NIKKI TAIT
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   NEW YORK
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
A US federal court in Atlanta has given final approval to the settlement of
a class-action lawsuit against the main US airlines which centred on
allegations of illegal ticket price-setting through use of a computerised
reservation system.
Most of the carriers settled the suit last summer, without admitting
liability, and will pay out an aggregate Dollars 458m (Pounds 322m) - most
of it through discount coupons for future air travel.
Under the settlement, virtually anyone who took a domestic flight between
January 1 1988, and June 30 1992 can apply to share in the settlement pool.
The deadline for claims is June 1.
