FT  24 MAR 93 / UN envoy restarts Haiti peace effort
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By REUTER
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   PORT-AU-PRINCE
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
THE United Nations special envoy to Haiti, Mr Dante Caputo, yesterday
resumed his attempt to set up negotiations on restoring democracy to the
island after the September 1991 military coup, Reuter reports from
Port-au-Prince.
Mr Caputo's visit follows that of Mr Lawrence Pezzullo, the Clinton
administration's special adviser on Haiti. Mr Pezzullo told the military and
the de facto civilian government the US was determined to restore democracy
swiftly.
In prior visits, Mr Caputo has stressed that his first task to persuade all
the parties to agree to the principle of negotiations and to accept the
Organisation of American States-UN joint human rights monitoring mission.
