<HEADLINE>
FT  24 MAR 93 / Russia in Crisis: Tension rises in Ukraine
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By JOHN LLOYD
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
THE shock waves caused by the spiralling crisis in Russia rolled over the
neighbouring state of Ukraine yesterday when a senior parliamentary figure
said Ukraine could not now rid itself of nuclear weapons while Russia
constituted such an unstable neighbour, writes John Lloyd.
Mr Dmytro Pavlychko, influential head of the foreign affairs committee, said
that while Ukraine would sign the start treaties, 'we can rule out joining
the Nuclear Non-Proliferation Treaty, which makes Ukraine a non-nuclear
state, primarily because of the situation in Russia'.
