FT  24 MAR 93 / Observer: BT's animal magic
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
The new symbol for the Share Shops handling the forthcoming sale of the
government's BT stock remains a state secret. But Observer hears that there
is a good chance that it will involve a bull and a bear.
The public has to be made aware that the market for shares goes down as well
as up - hence the need for the services of the stock market's two best-known
animals. However, the finer details of the symbol still have to be worked
out. Suggestions that the bull may be pictured dominating the bear may be
ruled out on grounds of good taste - although 'that's what we hope will
happen in the sale,' says one of the government's advisers.
