FT  24 MAR 93 / Letter: Union vote
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   From Sir DERMOT DE TRAFFORD
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Sir, Mr Julian Smith's example (Letters, March 19) of the ludicrous results
possible under the German system of proportional representation should not
blind anyone to the obvious merits of the single transferrable vote.
This preserves constituencies and ensures that the most popular candidate
wins the seat. It is happily accepted and works well in the Oxford and
Cambridge Unions.
Dermot de Trafford,
The Old Vicarage,
Appleshaw,
Andover,
Hants
