<HEADLINE>
FT  24 MAR 93 / People: Geographical divide at SmithKline
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
SmithKline Beecham, the Anglo-American drugs and consumer products group,
has reorganised its European and intercontinental pharmaceuticals
operations.
Bradley Wilson has been appointed chairman of the European drugs business.
His responsibilities will include eastern Europe, previously included in
intercontinental. Wilson, 46, was previously senior vice-president of the
intercontinental division, which covers Japan, the Pacific, Africa, the
Middle East, Latin America and India, which has been renamed the
international division. He replaces Charles Woler, who has resigned for
family reasons.
Mitchell Cybulski, also 46, previously senior vice-president Japan and
Pacific, has been appointed chairman of the new international division. He
joined SmithKline from Bristol-Myers Squibb in 1991.
