<HEADLINE>
FT  23 MAR 93 / World Trade News: Westinghouse joins Finnish group to bid
for power contracts
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By ANDREW BAXTER
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
WESTINGHOUSE Electric of the US and Finland's Haka-Stroi have formed a
co-operation agreement to identify, develop and supply power generation
projects in the Baltic countries and the Commonwealth of Independent States.
Westinghouse, one of the world's main suppliers of power generation plant,
will supply the power island and related equipment for each project under
the two-year deal.
Haka-Stroi, a civil engineering company, will manage plant construction
activities. It is a subsidiary of Haka, a big Finnish construction company
which has been active in CIS markets for 20 years.
Babcock International has won contracts worth about Pounds 30m for boiler
repair work in Kuwait and ship unloading and bulk materials handling
equipment from customers in Germany, Italy, Sweden, Taiwan and Thailand.
The deals include a Pounds 10m order from Kuwait's Ministry of Electricity
and Water for the reconstruction of three boilers at Shuwaikh Power Station,
which were extensively damaged during the Iraqi invasion.
GEC Alsthom Electromecanique, a Quebec-based subsidiary of the Anglo-French
engineering group, has won an order from Korea Heavy Industries &amp;
Construction to supply a nuclear reactor calandria for the Wolsong IV power
station in the south-east of South Korea.
