FT  23 MAR 93 / International Company News: Parker Pen deal threatened
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By LISA BRANSTEN
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   WASHINGTON
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
THE US Department of Justice announced yesterday it would file an anti-trust
suit to prevent Boston-based Gillette from purchasing Parker Pen on the
grounds that such a sale would have an anti-competitive effect on the market
for premium fountain pens, writes Lisa Bransten in Washington.
The suit could block Gillette's attempt to become the world's largest seller
of all types of pens. Gillette holds approximately 7 per cent of the world
pen market, while its leading competitor, Societe BIC, holds about 8 per
cent.
With Parker, Gillette would control 15 per cent of the world market. The
Justice Department contends that Gillette and Parker, together with one
other company, control 80 per cent of the premium fountain pen market.
